    <exercise id="fs-id1222134" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id2097299">
<para id="import-auto-id1523715">Which of the particles in <link target-id="import-auto-id2208173"/> has the greatest velocity, assuming they have identical charges and masses?</para><figure id="import-auto-id2208173"><media id="import-auto-id1525240" alt="Diagram showing magnetic field lines out of the page. Charge a curves clockwise with a large radius as it moves from the bottom to the top of the diagram. Charge b curves clockwise with a much smaller radius as it moves from lower middle to upper middle of the diagram.">
        <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/Figure_23_99_02a.jpg" width="150"/>
